				created_on: '2022-12-02T14:38:33.267Z',
				text: '<h1><strong>Background</strong></h1>\n<p>South Africa, especially Cape Town, has faced a myriad of issues, both stemming from historical injustices to current socioeconomic instability. Cape Town, like many Southern African cities was facing a major drought in 2018, leading extreme water insecurity. A looming <u>Day Zero</u> in which there would be no water for consumption within the city seemed to be on the horizon for Cape Town. In this situation, the gap between the impoverished and the wealthy were prevalent with the building of private wells, purchasing of inflated-priced water bottles, and even paying water-usage fines being undertaken by those who could afford to while those who could not were left in the hands of the government.</p>',
