				created_on: '2022-12-02T16:59:35.324Z',
				text: '<p>While water security is something to be celebrated, it was not the end to the issues facing Cape Town. From the start of the pandemic in 2020, homelessness has been rising with some local estimations of 300 percent increases. Similar to the water insecurity situation and many of the issues faced in South Africa, it comes down to the have&rsquo;s and the have-not&rsquo;s, whether that be political power seen in deeply racist history or the current wide gap between socioeconomic groups.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',
